# ── GearMedic / agent POST: one password, any text you like ───────────────────
# Same string here, in your host (e.g. Vercel) env, and in GearMedic as:
#   Authorization: Bearer <that same string>
# Pick something simple if you want, e.g. abs123  (fine for personal / test sites)
INGEST_PASSWORD=
# Older names still work if you already use them:
# AGENT_INGEST_SECRET=
# XALURA_INGEST_TOKEN=
# XALURA_AGENT_BEARER=

# (GearMedic / KV ingest — phaseout; ignore unless you still run that path.)
# KV_REST_API_URL=
# KV_REST_API_TOKEN=
# GET /api/ingest-health after deploy to verify KV + password are picked up

# Optional: until first approve/decline in Admin, POST may work without Bearer
# After that, Bearer (INGEST_PASSWORD) is required unless you set:
# AGENT_UPDATE_OPEN_INGEST=true
# Testing only — wrong password still inserts pending row:
# AGENT_UPDATE_ACCEPT_ANY=true

# ── Xalura agentic (xalura-agentic/) — Phases 1–7 (see docs/agentic-workflow-architecture-log.md) ──
# Docs: docs/agentic-workflow-architecture-log.md
#
# Minimum to turn on real LLM (Worker/Manager/Executive paths in pipelines):
# Paste your key from Google AI Studio — never commit real keys to the repo.
GEMINI_API_KEY=
# Optional model id (default in code: gemini-2.5-flash-lite):
GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash-lite
# Optional resilience (Phase 6 — lib/gemini.ts):
AGENTIC_GEMINI_TIMEOUT_MS=60000
AGENTIC_GEMINI_RETRIES=3
#
# If GEMINI_API_KEY is empty, pipelines still run with stubs (Manager can APPROVE).
# Set the same vars on Cloudflare (Workers) for /api/agentic-health gemini_configured: true.
# Must be on the **deployed Worker** (OpenNext / wrangler name), not only “build” env in CI.
#
# Optional: shown in `/api/agentic-health` `deploy_fingerprint` when CI does not set a commit env var.
BUILD_REF=

# One-time debugging (no key values returned): set a random string here and on Cloudflare, then:
#   GET /api/agentic-health?debug=<that same string>
# Response may include `gemini_env_debug` (booleans + typeof binding + truncated errors). Remove token when done.
AGENTIC_HEALTH_DEBUG_TOKEN=
#
# Optional live Gemini proof (one generateContent; uses API quota — do not put on dumb uptime polls):
#   GET /api/agentic-health?gemini_ping=1   (also: true, yes)
# Optional timeout for that call only (default 20000 ms):
# AGENTIC_GEMINI_PING_TIMEOUT_MS=20000
#
# Admin AI dashboard: publishing cadence bar (ms). Default 7200000 = 2h wall-clock slots (display only).
# AGENTIC_DASHBOARD_PUBLISH_CYCLE_MS=7200000
#
# Cloudflare **cron** (see `wrangler.jsonc` + `cloudflare/custom-worker.ts`) — all use Bearer `AGENTIC_CRON_SECRET`:
# - **Hourly** `0 * * * *` → `POST /api/cron/agentic-incremental` — one vertical (round-robin): SEO (topic bank) → Publishing → optional site upsert. Serp refresh obeys `AGENTIC_TOPIC_BANK_MIN_SERP_INTERVAL_HOURS` (default **72** = 3 days) so the same ~20-topic bank is consumed between refills.
# - **Every 10 min** `*/10 * * * *` → `POST /api/cron/agentic-chief-sweep` — Chief AI reads cycle + trend/event snapshot (no Serp); appends a line to `xalura-agentic/state/chief-sweep-log.jsonl`.
# - **Every 2h** `0 */2 * * *` → `POST /api/cron/agentic-publish` — legacy publishing-only + site upsert (same as before).
# Optional incremental tuning:
# AGENTIC_TOPIC_BANK_MIN_SERP_INTERVAL_HOURS=72
# AGENTIC_INCREMENTAL_SEO_TASK=…   (override default SEO brief for hourly tick)
# AGENTIC_INCREMENTAL_PUBLISH_TASK=… (override default article brief)
# AGENTIC_INCREMENTAL_AUTO_SITE_PUBLISH=true|false — default follows `AGENTIC_AUTO_PUBLISH_TO_SITE` when unset.
# Local: `npm run agentic:incremental-once` (uses `.env.local` like other smokes).
# Topic bank: default is `xalura-agentic/state/topic-bank.json` (needs writable disk). On read-only hosts (e.g. Cloudflare Workers), persist the bank in Supabase instead:
# AGENTIC_TOPIC_BANK_USE_SUPABASE=true
# Requires `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` + `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` and table `public.agentic_topic_bank` (see `supabase/schema.sql`). When true, reads prefer Supabase then fall back to disk; writes go to Supabase and still mirror to disk when writable.
# wrangler secret put AGENTIC_CRON_SECRET   (strong random; NOT the same as AGENTIC_RUN_TOKEN)
# Worker vars (dashboard → Settings → Variables, or wrangler vars):
# AGENTIC_CRON_BASE_URL=https://www.xaluratech.com   (origin only, no trailing slash; used by scheduled handler to self-fetch)
# If unset, scheduled handler falls back to AGENTIC_PUBLIC_BASE_URL then NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL.
# Optional override for the article brief each cron tick:
# AGENTIC_CRON_PUBLISH_TASK=Write a Markdown article about …
#
# POST /api/agentic/run — Bearer auth (run pipelines + optional Supabase publish):
# Prefer a dedicated secret (set on the Worker too):
# AGENTIC_RUN_TOKEN=
# If AGENTIC_RUN_TOKEN is unset, the same bearer as INGEST_PASSWORD is accepted.

# Phase 7 — HTTP clients in `xalura-agentic/lib/phase7Clients.ts` (health shows `phase7` flags):
# Pipelines: SEO Worker context pulls GSC top queries when OAuth + site URL are set; any department
# can pass JSON `referenceUrl` to POST /api/agentic/run for Firecrawl → Worker context.
# Marketing: after each approval, `GET …/profiles` (Zernio) — see `result.phase7.zernio` in API JSON.
# Publishing: after a successful Supabase article upsert, optional `POST …/v1/posts` when enabled — see `publish.zernio` in run JSON.
# AGENTIC_AUTO_PUBLISH_TO_SITE=true — approved publishing runs upsert `articles` without sending publishToSite:true (send publishToSite:false to opt out; never combine with useHandoff).
# AGENTIC_ZERNIO_POST_ON_PUBLISH=true — after site publish, call Zernio (needs ZERNIO_API_KEY plus queue or platforms below).
# AGENTIC_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=https://your-domain.com — public link in Zernio post (Workers: set this or NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL).
# ZERNIO_QUEUED_FROM_PROFILE_ID= — profile _id from GET /v1/profiles (queue draft path), **or**
# ZERNIO_POST_PLATFORMS_JSON=[{"platform":"twitter","accountId":"<account _id>"}] — immediate publishNow to those accounts.
# Alerts (optional Resend): failures appended to `failed/operations-queue.json` also email:
# AGENTIC_OPS_ALERT_EMAIL=you@example.com
# After Chief enriches a 10-cycle audit file on disk:
# AGENTIC_CHIEF_DIGEST_EMAIL=you@example.com
# After each successful **site publish** (publishToSite), optional Chief cycle digest to that same inbox:
# AGENTIC_CHIEF_EMAIL_ON_PUBLISH=true
# Compliance / founder email after each successful site publish (admin “Run & publish”, cron, or API — same code path). No veto. Includes Compliance Officer memo (scored rubric D1–D7 + counsel-style posture), risk level, draft email with **display-only** Cc: Chief AI, Executives (not Resend cc:). Uses waitUntil + Resend + Gemini flash-lite (+ optional Imagen):
# **Checklist — all must be true on the runtime that performs the publish** (Next.js vs Cloudflare Worker each has its own env):
# (1) AGENTIC_COMPLIANCE_ON_PUBLISH=true **or** AGENTIC_FOUNDER_OVERSIGHT_ON_PUBLISH=true
# (2) Inbox: AGENTIC_COMPLIANCE_EMAIL and/or AGENTIC_FOUNDER_OVERSIGHT_EMAIL and/or AGENTIC_CHIEF_DIGEST_EMAIL (fallback order)
# (3) RESEND_API_KEY (+ optional RESEND_FROM verified sender)
# (4) GEMINI_API_KEY (memo + analyst blocks; rubric is advisory, not legal advice)
# AGENTIC_COMPLIANCE_ON_PUBLISH=true
# AGENTIC_COMPLIANCE_EMAIL=you@example.com
# (Aliases — either on-flag or both can be set; email falls back in order:)
# AGENTIC_FOUNDER_OVERSIGHT_ON_PUBLISH=true
# AGENTIC_FOUNDER_OVERSIGHT_EMAIL=you@example.com
# (Blank compliance/founder email falls back to AGENTIC_CHIEF_DIGEST_EMAIL.)
# Optional hero image: flash-lite art brief → Imagen → **Supabase Storage** `article-covers` + `articles.cover_image_url`, and email attachment when compliance mail runs. Run the `article-covers` block in `supabase/schema.sql` (or Dashboard → Storage). On Cloudflare, `wrangler.jsonc` sets this to true by default; override in Dashboard if needed.
# AGENTIC_GRAPHIC_DESIGNER_ON_PUBLISH=true
# Optional strict mode: refuse the Supabase upsert unless a cover URL was produced (requires AGENTIC_GRAPHIC_DESIGNER_ON_PUBLISH=true and a working `article-covers` bucket):
# AGENTIC_REQUIRE_COVER_ON_PUBLISH=true
# Imagen model id (REST `:predict` — see `xalura-agentic/lib/imagenGenerate.ts`):
# AGENTIC_IMAGE_MODEL=imagen-4.0-ultra-generate-001
# RESEND_API_KEY=
# Optional verified sender (default many accounts use for tests: onboarding@resend.dev):
# RESEND_FROM=onboarding@resend.dev
#
# Resend inbound → Chief replies by email (POST /api/webhooks/resend-chief-inbound):
# In Resend: enable Receiving, add webhook `email.received`, copy signing secret:
# RESEND_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
# Comma-separated From addresses allowed to get a Chief reply (required; empty = no replies):
# CHIEF_INBOUND_ALLOWED_SENDERS=you@example.com
# Optional: only process mail whose To includes this substring (e.g. chief@yourdomain.com):
# CHIEF_INBOUND_TO_FILTER=chief@
# FIRECRAWL_API_KEY=
# Optional override (default https://api.firecrawl.dev):
# FIRECRAWL_BASE_URL=
# ZERNIO_API_KEY=
# Optional API root (default https://zernio.com/api):
# ZERNIO_API_BASE=
# Topic bank “web search” uses **SerpAPI** (not Google Custom Search). Key: https://serpapi.com/manage-api-key
# SERPAPI_API_KEY=
# Optional engine id for SerpAPI (default: google): SERPAPI_ENGINE=google
# Smoke: npm run agentic:diagnose-serpapi
# POST /api/agentic/content/refresh-topic-bank — same Bearer as agentic run (forces new bank).
# Each refresh: **one Serp call** → ~20 ranked topics (all CONTENT_VERTICALS) + `xalura-agentic/state/seo-trend-logs.json`.
# POST /api/agentic/run JSON: `contentVerticalId` (e.g. `developer-tools-oss`) with `useTopicBank` (SEO) or publishing lane override.
# Each vertical id gets its **own** 10-cycle ladder + markdown under `xalura-agentic/logs/seo/lanes/{id}/` and `.../publishing/lanes/{id}/` (see `data/cycle-state.json` → `agentLanes`).

# Google Search Console — DIFFERENT product (analytics for YOUR site). Optional OAuth + site URL:
# GOOGLE_SC_CLIENT_ID=
# GOOGLE_SC_SECRET=
# GOOGLE_SC_REFRESH_TOKEN=
# GOOGLE_SC_SITE_URL=https://your-domain.com/

# Docs only — create admin in Supabase Auth
ADMIN_EMAIL=
ADMIN_PASSWORD=

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# BEGINNER TABLE — Variable | What you actually type (not all are required)
# Copy NAME=value lines into `.env.local`. Cloudflare: wrangler secret put NAME for secrets.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# | Variable                      | What to put |
# |-------------------------------|-------------|
# | AGENTIC_RUN_TOKEN             | Any strong random string YOU make up. Used as Bearer token for POST /api/agentic/run. Leave blank to reuse INGEST_PASSWORD as Bearer instead. |
# | GEMINI_MODEL                  | Optional. Exact model id string (e.g. gemini-2.5-flash-lite). Blank = code default. |
# | AGENTIC_GEMINI_TIMEOUT_MS     | Optional. Number only, e.g. 60000 (milliseconds). Blank = default in code. |
# | AGENTIC_GEMINI_RETRIES        | Optional. Number only, e.g. 3. Blank = default. |
# | AGENTIC_GEMINI_PING_TIMEOUT_MS | Optional. For /api/agentic-health?gemini_ping=1 only. Blank = default. |
# | BUILD_REF                     | Optional. Short text like a git commit or deploy label. Blank is OK. |
# | SERPAPI_API_KEY               | Secret from serpapi.com dashboard (topic bank + SEO `useTopicBank`). |
# | SERPAPI_ENGINE                | Optional. SerpAPI `engine` param; default `google`. |
# | FIRECRAWL_API_KEY             | Secret from firecrawl.dev dashboard. |
# | FIRECRAWL_BASE_URL            | Usually LEAVE BLANK. Only set if Firecrawl gave you a custom API base (otherwise default is https://api.firecrawl.dev). |
# | GOOGLE_SC_CLIENT_ID           | OAuth “Client ID” string from Google Cloud (Search Console API access). Optional. |
# | GOOGLE_SC_SECRET              | OAuth “Client secret” from same client. Optional. |
# | GOOGLE_SC_REFRESH_TOKEN       | One long token from OAuth flow with offline access — not a URL. Optional. |
# | GOOGLE_SC_SITE_URL            | Your property URL exactly as in Search Console, e.g. https://example.com/ — not an API path. |
# | RESEND_API_KEY                | Secret from resend.com (starts with re_). |
# | RESEND_FROM                   | An email you’re allowed to send from in Resend (verified sender). Can be blank for dev default in code. |
# | RESEND_WEBHOOK_SECRET         | From Resend webhook settings (Svix signing secret) for inbound Chief email. |
# | CHIEF_INBOUND_ALLOWED_SENDERS | Comma-separated sender emails that may email Chief and receive a reply. Required for inbound replies. |
# | CHIEF_INBOUND_TO_FILTER       | Optional substring; if set, webhook only runs when a To address contains it (e.g. chief@). |
# | AGENTIC_OPS_ALERT_EMAIL       | YOUR email address to receive failure alerts (plain email, not a secret). |
# | AGENTIC_CHIEF_DIGEST_EMAIL     | YOUR email for optional Chief audit notifications. |
# | AGENTIC_CHIEF_EMAIL_ON_PUBLISH | true = email Chief digest after each successful article publish (needs digest email + Resend + Gemini for best text). |
# | AGENTIC_COMPLIANCE_ON_PUBLISH | true = email compliance report after each successful publish (same as founder oversight path). |
# | AGENTIC_COMPLIANCE_EMAIL | Inbox for that report; blank → AGENTIC_FOUNDER_OVERSIGHT_EMAIL → AGENTIC_CHIEF_DIGEST_EMAIL. |
# | AGENTIC_FOUNDER_OVERSIGHT_ON_PUBLISH | true = same email pipeline as compliance (either flag may be used). |
# | AGENTIC_FOUNDER_OVERSIGHT_EMAIL | Inbox when compliance email blank; else chief digest email. |
# | AGENTIC_GRAPHIC_DESIGNER_ON_PUBLISH | true = attach optional hero PNG from Imagen (same GEMINI_API_KEY). |
# | AGENTIC_IMAGE_MODEL           | Imagen model id for generateImages; default imagen-4.0-ultra-generate-001. |
# | ZERNIO_API_KEY                | Secret API key from Zernio. Optional. |
# | ZERNIO_API_BASE               | Almost always LEAVE BLANK. Only if Zernio gave a custom API root URL (otherwise code uses default host). |
# | AGENTIC_AUTO_PUBLISH_TO_SITE  | true = publishing + approved → Supabase upsert without publishToSite in JSON; false/blank = only when body has publishToSite:true. |
# | AGENTIC_ZERNIO_POST_ON_PUBLISH | true = after successful site publish, POST to Zernio /v1/posts (needs ZERNIO_QUEUED_FROM_PROFILE_ID or ZERNIO_POST_PLATFORMS_JSON). |
# | AGENTIC_PUBLIC_BASE_URL       | Canonical site URL for links in Zernio posts, e.g. https://xalura.com — prefer on Cloudflare Workers if NEXT_PUBLIC_* is build-only. |
# | AGENTIC_CRON_SECRET           | Strong random string. Bearer for POST /api/cron/agentic-publish and for the Worker scheduled self-fetch. wrangler secret put. |
# | AGENTIC_CRON_BASE_URL         | Public site origin only, e.g. https://www.xaluratech.com — Worker cron uses this to call /api/cron/agentic-publish. Plain var (not secret). |
# | AGENTIC_CRON_PUBLISH_TASK     | Optional. Overrides the publishing `task` string for each cron run (else same default as admin publish). |
# | ZERNIO_QUEUED_FROM_PROFILE_ID | Zernio profile _id for queuedFromProfile (see Zernio create-post docs). |
# | ZERNIO_POST_PLATFORMS_JSON    | JSON array of { platform, accountId } for publishNow multi-platform posts. |
#
